{"article_id":"GWZvJ77qOqQ8EspW","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"It was a leak","depth":9},{"id":1,"text":"clearly designed to make William Barr 's day on Capitol Hill far more unpleasant .","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"The source or sources","depth":12},{"id":3,"text":"who showed The Washington Post a letter of complaint","depth":13},{"id":4,"text":"that Bob Mueller had written Barr","depth":13},{"id":5,"text":"created a media explosion","depth":12},{"id":6,"text":"that reverberated all day yesterday ,","depth":13},{"id":7,"text":"when the attorney general had been slated to testify before a Senate committee .","depth":13},{"id":8,"text":"Even before he took the hot seat ,","depth":12},{"id":9,"text":"some Democrats were calling on Barr to resign","depth":13},{"id":10,"text":"- which has virtually no chance","depth":14},{"id":11,"text":"of happening .","depth":14},{"id":12,"text":"Once the Judiciary Committee hearing got underway ,","depth":14},{"id":13,"text":"it was so utterly partisan","depth":14},{"id":14,"text":"that it seemed Republicans and Democrats were operating in parallel universes -","depth":13},{"id":15,"text":"and that tended to muffle the uproar over the once-secret Mueller letter .","depth":12},{"id":16,"text":"Still , the letter hurts Barr 's reputation ,","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"no question about it .","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"The missive provides ammunition to the AG 's critics ,","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"who say","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"he acted like a Trump partisan","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"in spinning and perhaps minimizing the Mueller report 's findings .","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"But let 's face it :","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"the special counsel 's letter would have been far more damaging","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"had it emerged","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"before the report was made public ,","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"when the debate over Barr 's conduct was at its peak .","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"Now that we 've all had the 448-page report for a couple of weeks ,","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"this has the feel","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"of relitigating a process question","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"that 's been overtaken by events .","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"`` The letter and a subsequent phone call between the two men reveal the degree","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"to which the longtime colleagues and friends disagreed","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"as they handled the legally and politically fraught task","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"of investigating the president , ''","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"the Post says .","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"The paper quotes the Mueller note","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"as dissing Barr 's famous four-page summary","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"before the report was out :","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"`` The summary letter","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"the Department sent to Congress","depth":13},{"id":41,"text":"and released to the public late in the afternoon of March 24","depth":13},{"id":42,"text":"did not fully capture the context , nature , and substance of this office 's work and conclusions .","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"There is now public confusion about critical aspects of the results of our investigation .","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"This threatens to undermine a central purpose","depth":13},{"id":45,"text":"for which the Department appointed the Special Counsel :","depth":13},{"id":46,"text":"to assure full public confidence in the outcome of the investigations . ''","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"Mueller asked","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"that his own executive summaries be quickly released ,","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"but Barr declined .","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"BARR ACCUSES DEMS OF USING CRIMINAL JUSTICE PROCESS AS 'POLITICAL WEAPON '","depth":5},{"id":51,"text":"AS HEARING TENSIONS FLARE","depth":5},{"id":52,"text":"One reason","depth":5},{"id":53,"text":"the leaked letter landed with considerable force","depth":5},{"id":54,"text":"is that we never hear Mueller express opinions in his own voice , rather than in legal filings or the rare statements from his office .","depth":5},{"id":55,"text":"He is the offstage presence , the opposite of a grandstander ,","depth":6},{"id":56,"text":"even with the report having been made published .","depth":6},{"id":57,"text":"The public will finally hear Mueller speak in House testimony this month ,","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"according to an agreement","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"announced yesterday .","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"But clearly one of his allies","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"- whether it was with Mueller 's acquiescence or not ,","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"we do n't know -","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"wanted to turn up the heat before Barr 's testimony .","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"The GOP side ,","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"led by Lindsey Graham ,","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"mainly wanted to talk about Hillary Clinton 's emails and Trump-sliming emails from the FBI 's Peter Strzok and Lisa Page","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"( complete with an F-word","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"that the senator read on live television ) .","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"The Democratic side ,","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"led by Dianne Feinstein ,","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"read damaging passages from the report","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"and pressed Barr about his disagreements with Mueller and why he did n't see many of the findings as obstruction of justice .","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"What was most noteworthy was Barr admitting","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"he was surprised","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"when Mueller declined to reach a conclusion on obstruction allegations","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"and saying","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"he could not get a clear explanation","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"while meeting with him .","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"The implication was that Mueller ,","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"given his independence ,","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"should have made the call ,","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"and instead made the report what Barr called `` my baby . ''","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"The attorney general insisted","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"that Mueller `` was very clear with me","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"that he was not suggesting","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"that we had misrepresented his report . ''","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"In a shot at the media , Barr said","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"Mueller told him","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"that `` the press reporting had been inaccurate","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"and that the press was reading too much into it . ''","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"Oddly enough , Barr also said","depth":7},{"id":92,"text":"Mueller declined his offer","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"to review the four-page summary in advance .","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"Feinstein pressed the AG about the finding","depth":6},{"id":95,"text":"that Trump told his White House counsel , Don McGahn , to have Mueller fired ,","depth":7},{"id":96,"text":"and that McGahn refused","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"and threatened to resign .","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"This was not an attempt","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"to obstruct the probe ,","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"Barr said ,","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"because `` there is a distinction","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"between saying to someone ,","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"'Go fire him ,","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"go fire Mueller , '","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"and saying ,","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"'Have him removed","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"based on conflict . ' ''","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"But there was no obstruction ,","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"Barr said ,","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"because `` presumably '' someone else would have been named","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"to replace Mueller .","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"( McGahn regarded the conflict questions as `` silly . '' )","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"Things turned absurdly partisan","depth":5},{"id":114,"text":"when Sen. Mazie Hirono demanded","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"that Barr resign ,","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"saying","depth":8},{"id":117,"text":"he had sacrificed his `` once-decent reputation for the grifter and liar","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"who sits in the Oval Office . ''","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"Graham shot back ,","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"`` Listen ,","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"you slandered this man ! ''","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"And the three presidential candidates on the panel","depth":7},{"id":123,"text":"- Kamala Harris , Amy Klobuchar and Cory Booker -","depth":7},{"id":124,"text":"all got their licks in .","depth":6},{"id":125,"text":"Harris , Booker and former Vice President Joe Biden also demanded the AG 's resignation .","depth":5},{"id":126,"text":"In the end , the spat between Barr and Mueller will be a historical footnote .","depth":2},{"id":127,"text":"But it provides more fodder","depth":4},{"id":128,"text":"for the Democrats and Trump 's media critics","depth":4},{"id":129,"text":"to try to keep the investigation alive .","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":259,"left":255,"right":258,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":255,"left":186,"right":254,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":186,"left":181,"right":185,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":181,"left":179,"right":180,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":179,"left":176,"right":178,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":176,"left":151,"right":175,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":147,"right":150,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":131,"right":146,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":131,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":146,"left":144,"rig